text: Vít Jedlička (born 6 September 1983) is a Czech politician and the founder of Liberland. In 2008, Jedlička received a bachelor's degree in international relations and affairs from the University of Economics, Prague. He gained his master's degree in political science at the CEVRO Institute in 2014. Jedlička has worked in sales, management, financial analysis and in the IT sector.
